 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Notebook 3 — Tree Detection & Counting\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook applies three methods for detecting and counting trees,\n",
    "chosen based on the resolution of your available imagery:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Method | Imagery needed | What you get |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| **DeepForest** (Weinstein 2020) | ≤ 1 m (Cartosat-3, Planet) | Individual bounding boxes + count |\n",
    "| **U-Net segmentation** (Ronneberger 2015) | 5–10 m (LISS-IV, Sentinel-2) | Canopy mask → count via crown area |\n",
    "| **Watershed on NDVI** | 5–30 m (any) | Crown patches → count |\n",
    "| **NDVI threshold + allometry** (Jucker 2017) | Any | Statistical estimate with CI |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, '..')\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import yaml\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "with open('../config.yaml') as f:\n",
    "    cfg = yaml.safe_load(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Analysis method:', cfg['analysis']['tree_detection_method'])\n",
    "print('NDVI threshold:', cfg['analysis']['vegetation_threshold'])\n",
    "print('Mean crown area:', cfg['analysis']['mean_crown_area_m2'], 'm²')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Method A — Watershed Segmentation (works with Sentinel-2 / LISS-IV)\n",
    "\n",
    "Uses local maxima in the NDVI surface as seed points, then applies\n",
    "watershed to delineate individual crown boundaries.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Reference**: Vincent & Soille (1991). *IEEE TPAMI*, 13(6), 583-598."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from src.preprocessing.image_utils import read_bands\n",
    "from src.analysis.indices import ndvi\n",
    "from src.analysis.tree_detection import detect_trees_watershed, estimate_tree_count_from_canopy\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load your current-period image (update path after downloading)\n",
    "# current_path = Path('../data/raw/sentinel2/2024/your_file.tif')\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- Demo: create synthetic NDVI for illustration ---\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "H, W = 256, 256\n",
    "ndvi_demo = np.zeros((H, W), dtype=np.float32)\n",
    "# Add Gaussian 'trees' to simulate canopy NDVI peaks\n",
    "from scipy.ndimage import gaussian_filter\n",
    "for _ in range(120):\n",
    "    r, c = np.random.randint(10, H-10), np.random.randint(10, W-10)\n",
    "    crown = np.zeros((H, W))\n",
    "    crown[r, c] = 1.0\n",
    "    crown = gaussian_filter(crown, sigma=np.random.uniform(2, 5))\n",
    "    ndvi_demo += crown * np.random.uniform(0.5, 0.85)\n",
    "ndvi_demo = np.clip(ndvi_demo, 0, 1)\n",
    "ndvi_demo += np.random.normal(0, 0.02, (H, W))\n",
    "ndvi_demo = np.clip(ndvi_demo, 0, 1)\n",
    "pixel_size_m = 5.8  # LISS-IV resolution\n",
    "print('Synthetic NDVI shape:', ndvi_demo.shape)\n",
    "print('Mean NDVI:', ndvi_demo.mean().round(3))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Run watershed tree detection\n",
    "labels, n_detected = detect_trees_watershed(\n",
    "    ndvi_array=ndvi_demo,\n",
    "    pixel_size_m=pixel_size_m,\n",
    "    min_crown_area_m2=10.0,\n",
    "    smoothing_sigma=1.5,\n",
    "    ndvi_threshold=0.30,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'\\nWatershed result: {n_detected} tree crowns detected')\n",
    "print(f'Image area: {H * W * pixel_size_m**2 / 10000:.2f} ha')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualise watershed results\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(15, 5))\n",
    "fig.suptitle('Watershed Tree Crown Detection', fontsize=13, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "im0 = axes[0].imshow(ndvi_demo, cmap='RdYlGn', vmin=0, vmax=0.9)\n",
    "axes[0].set_title(f'NDVI ({pixel_size_m} m resolution)')\n",
    "plt.colorbar(im0, ax=axes[0], label='NDVI')\n",
    "\n",
    "im1 = axes[1].imshow(labels > 0, cmap='Greens')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Canopy Mask (NDVI > 0.30)')\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.colors as mcolors\n",
    "cmap_labels = plt.cm.get_cmap('nipy_spectral', n_detected + 1)\n",
    "label_display = labels.copy().astype(float)\n",
    "label_display[labels == 0] = np.nan\n",
    "im2 = axes[2].imshow(label_display, cmap=cmap_labels, vmin=0, vmax=n_detected)\n",
    "axes[2].set_title(f'Detected Crowns: {n_detected} trees')\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax in axes:\n",
    "    ax.axis('off')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('../results/watershed_detection.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Method B — Allometric Estimate from NDVI\n",
    "\n",
    "For medium-resolution imagery (10–30 m) where individual crowns are not\n",
    "resolvable, estimate tree count from total canopy area.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Reference**: Jucker, T. et al. (2017). *Global Change Biology*, 23(1), 177-190."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from src.analysis.tree_detection import estimate_tree_count_from_canopy\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate canopy area from NDVI mask\n",
    "veg_mask = ndvi_demo > 0.35\n",
    "canopy_area_m2 = float(veg_mask.sum()) * (pixel_size_m ** 2)\n",
    "canopy_area_ha = canopy_area_m2 / 10_000\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Vegetated pixels: {veg_mask.sum():,} ({veg_mask.mean()*100:.1f}% of image)')\n",
    "print(f'Canopy area: {canopy_area_ha:.2f} ha')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Allometric estimate for different biomes\n",
    "for biome in ['tropical_dry', 'tropical_wet', 'subtropical', 'urban']:\n",
    "    est = estimate_tree_count_from_canopy(canopy_area_m2, biome=biome)\n",
    "    print(f'  {biome:16s}: {est[\"estimate\"]:,} trees '\n",
    "          f'[95% CI: {est[\"lower_95ci\"]:,} – {est[\"upper_95ci\"]:,}]')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Method C — DeepForest (requires ≤ 1 m imagery)\n",
    "\n",
    "For Cartosat-3 (0.25 m), Planet (3 m), or drone imagery.\n",
    "Runs a RetinaNet detector pretrained on NEON airborne data.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Reference**: Weinstein, B.G. et al. (2020). *Methods in Ecology and Evolution*, 11, 1743-1751."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Uncomment when high-resolution imagery is available:\n",
