    "# )\n",
    "# print(f'DeepForest detected {len(crowns)} trees')\n",
    "# crowns.to_file('../data/processed/crowns/deepforest_crowns.geojson', driver='GeoJSON')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('DeepForest ready — provide Cartosat-3 or Planet imagery to run.')\n",
    "print('Download NEON pretrained weights automatically on first run.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "| Method | Trees detected | Notes |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Watershed (5.8 m) | From watershed | Works on LISS-IV |\n",
    "| Allometric (tropical_dry) | Statistical estimate | Use for medium-res imagery |\n",
    "| DeepForest (≤1m) | Individual crowns | Needs Cartosat-3 / Planet |\n",
    "\n",
    "Next: **Notebook 4 — Change Detection** to compare tree counts across time."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Save detection results\n",
    "Path('../results').mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n",
    "results = {\n",
    "    'method': 'watershed',\n",
    "    'pixel_size_m': pixel_size_m,\n",
    "    'n_trees_detected': int(n_detected),\n",
    "    'canopy_area_ha': round(canopy_area_ha, 2),\n",
    "    'allometric_estimate': estimate_tree_count_from_canopy(\n",
    "        canopy_area_m2, biome='tropical_dry'\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "}\n",
    "import json\n",
    "with open('../results/tree_detection_current.json', 'w') as f:\n",
    "    json.dump(results, f, indent=2)\n",
    "print('Results saved to results/tree_detection_current.json')"
   ]
  }
 ],
